    {
      "topic": "Pre-Requisites",
      "items": [
        {
          "title": "<p>This utility can currently only be used for JavaScript/Node projects.</p>"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "topic": "Install",
      "items": [
        {
          "title": "<p>This utility can be used as a temporary dependency, global dependency or a dev dependency.</p><p>Head over to the <a href=\"##usage\">usage</a> section below on how to set it up based on your preference.</p>"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "topic": "Usage",
      "items": [
        {
          "topic": "Parameters",
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "<p>The utility accepts the following parameters:</p>"
            },
            {
              "title": "--path - to specify the path of your project directory (defaults to current working directory)"
            },
            {
              "title": "--org - to specify the npm organization namespace for your project"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "topic": "Usage as a temporary dependency",
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "<p>This is great option for taking this a quick spin!</p><pre><code>npx @condenast/opensource-check --path &lt;your-project-path&gt;\nnpx @condenast/opensource-check --path ./glamorous\nnpx @condenast/opensource-check --path ./xml-to-react --org condenast\n</code></pre>"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "topic": "Usage as a global dependency",
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "<p>This is a good option if you plan to use this frequently but don't want it to be a part of your project setup.</p><pre><code>npm install -g @condenast/opensource-check\n\nopensource-check --path &lt;your-project-path&gt;\nopensource-check --path ./glamorous\nopensource-check --path ./xml-to-react --org condenast\n</code></pre>"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "topic": "Usage as a dev dependency",
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "<p>This is a wonderful option if you plan to use this as part of your project workflow including using in CI environment.</p><pre><code>npm install -D @condenast/opensource-check\n\nnpx @condenast/opensource-check --path &lt;your-project-path&gt;\nnpx @condenast/opensource-check --path ./glamorous\nnpx @condenast/opensource-check --path ./xml-to-react --org condenast\n</code></pre>"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "topic": "Screenshot",
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "<p>This is a sample screenshot of running this utlility:</p><p><img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1215971/37443485-74f4b324-27da-11e8-9e77-957de7edaec8.png\" title=\"screenshot\" width=\"350/\"/></p>"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
